    <h2 style="color:pink">Answer</h2>
<p style=" border:5px dotted pink;">
    1. If I use the term "all", I can delete "color 0.2s linear" in the following code: "transition: background .3s ease, color 0.2s linear<br>
    2. I will need to know the terms when learning the transition. I know that ease starts at a slow speed, then becomes faster, and then ends slowly. And liner stays at the same speed. Ease-in and ease-out are similar, but ease-in starts at a slow speed, and ease-out ends at a slow speed. Gradually, it starts slowly and ends slowly. The last item is the cubic-bezier, which specifies your own transition look value.
</p>

